@Mynameislegion: I can appreciate that, though I prefer a bit more contrast and Teal/Beige isn't my preferred color scheme. Darker blues are my personal favorites, despite what DZM's current theme might suggest, but I scrapped blue because it has a tendency to disappear when using screen tinters like "f.lux". The original purpose of DZM was, as it's name suggests, to provide a Dark mode for people in dim environments, or for nighttime viewing. Sadly, your suggested color scheme doesn't fit with those requirements.

Though I suppose I could create a separate T/B themed ZeroMe, but it isn't a priority at the moment.

As for going material theme, that's even more work, but sounds interesting. However, again, not a priority for me right now.

@Scrub: It would be nice, but would require a lot of JS work(Not my strong suit). 

The complicated part of ZeroMe is that most of the site is generated dynamically from "all.js". I can't just change things around in there all willynilly as it would make it harder to merge upstream changes in ZeroMe. So I have to look at and understand how and why "all.js" does things before I can start making major changes.

My goal isn't to make a new ZeroMe front-end, I sadly don't have the time to support that. What I can do is tweak the current ZeroMe front-end, and keep it up-to-date with the latest changes in ZeroMe. You'll have to ask someone else, or figure it out on your own, if you want anything more complicated done.

